data.name: Spinach and Strawberry Salad with Balsamic Dressing
data.quickTastyDescription: A refreshing and vibrant salad combining fresh spinach, juicy strawberries, and a tangy balsamic dressing, perfect for a light meal or side dish.
detailedCookingInstructions: Wash the spinach thoroughly and place it in a large salad bowl.
Slice the strawberries and add them to the bowl with the spinach.
Crumble feta cheese over the top of the salad.
Chop the walnuts and sprinkle them on the salad.
In a small bowl, whisk together balsamic vinegar, olive oil, honey, salt, and black pepper to create the dressing.
Drizzle the dressing over the salad and toss gently to combine.
